Lexy Wood apologized to Rebecca Boyd after she disrupted a movie screening of Cinderella in Alabama . 
  Her mother Kyesha Smith Wood posted a message on Facebook saying she was 'embarrassed' by her daughters behavior . 
  Boyd was watching the movie with her daughter Ashley and her husband had just been laid off . 
  She confronted Lexy and her brother Nick after the movie and said they were 'rude and obnoxious' Mrs Wood said she would pay for her next movie trip out of her children's allowance . 
  She apologized to Boyd on Inside Edition and said she was embarrassed . 
  Boyd said that the apology 'reminded me that there are still good people in the world'